Obligating your success is great strategy. Setting up your life where you have no choice but to accomplish your goals. I have tax dates on my calendar. Certain periods I’m preparing for it. I pay a lot of taxes. So more tax efficient I can be the better. Being on time for taxes is half the battle. Keeping good records, and having basic understanding of the tax code is important. Making it a part of your life. It’s really expensive if you ignore it, if you lie, if you don’t pay, or if you don’t take advantage of tax credits or deductions. 
.
The government creates tax deductions and credits to direct funds into those area of the economy. Seriously 😐 there are vehicles that give you incredible tax deductions and some that give you zero. 
.
There are ways to sell property like a 1031x exchange that make the sell of a property tax free, if you follow rules and guidelines. I’ve done it many times. 
.
Big difference in paying $100k taxes and paying zero in taxes and rolling your money into larger, more valuable asset that produces tax free cash flow. 😳 seriously 😐 having basic understanding of tax code could make you (save) a lot of money. 

Knowing when quarterly payments are due, paying on time. You owe on every dollar 💵 you make in labor and profit once you pass the line of poverty where you’re not taxed. So learning is important for everyone. Even if you use an account learn more about the game of taxes. It Can Pays huge if you do. 
Seriously 😐 huge. 
.
Setting aside money in segregated account just to pay taxes obligates you to staying on top your game. Get on it 💪👑
